Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,=20
Happy Wednesday! Last week, I promised you an essay on Grand Strategy, and =
that=E2=80=99s coming, but while writing it, I opened Twitter and I learned=
 something odd=E2=80=A6=20
Crypto seems to be not dead.=20
It=E2=80=99s weird because I could have sworn people said it was dead, that=
 if you=E2=80=99re in crypto, you should pivot to AI. And yet, here we are.=
=20
Now who knows if this recent run-up is the beginning of a new bull market o=
r just a little glimmer of hope in the middle of a long bear. Certainly not=
 me. Long-term, price matters only insofar as it attracts developers to the=
 space to build good products.=20
Crypto is often viewed as this ideological thing. You either love it or hat=
e it. But I think a more useful way to think about the space is that blockc=
hains are just platforms. In their current state, they present unique benef=
its and real drawbacks.=20
Ultimately, developers will choose to build on blockchains if the benefits =
outweigh the drawbacks for the specific product they=E2=80=99re trying to b=
uild. It=E2=80=99s that simple.=20
If this is the end of the bear market, it seems odd that it=E2=80=99s come =
without new killer use cases. My guess is that higher prices will make deve=
lopers take another look at blockchains, and that when they do, a larger nu=
mber will find that the trade-offs make sense for what they=E2=80=99re tryi=
ng to build.=20
This is a shorter one, so if you=E2=80=99re looking for something to fill t=
he void, Age of Miracles [ https://substack.com/redirect/d7428680-8162-49cd=
