olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margi=
n-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Stigmatization &#8594; will come with more=
 good products&#160;</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There&#8217;s still a t=
on of improvement left to be made. Onchain actions need to get nearly as ch=
eap as fast as offchain actions for the benefits to outweigh the drawbacks =
for many use cases. Developers will need to be thoughtful about which actio=
ns need to be onchain, which can take place offchain, and the best ways to =
build experiences that combine the two.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64,=
 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We&#8217=
;ll likely never get to a world in which everything is built onchain. For s=
ome products, crypto&#8217;s benefits might not matter and might even be co=
unterproductive. That&#8217;s OK.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But over time,=
 as infrastructure developers attack crypto&#8217;s drawbacks, and app deve=
lopers get crypto&#8217;s benefits for closer to free, I expect that we&#82=
17;ll see a surprising amount of products move onchain.</p><div style=3D"fo=
